cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >
  Bu açık eğitim kaynağını kullanıyorsanız lütfen aşağıdaki şekilde kaynak gösterin.
  If you use this open educational resource, please cite it as below.
title: "PyTorch Eğitim Kaynakları (PyTorch Education Open Educational Resource)"
abstract: >
  An open educational resource written in Turkish to teach PyTorch fundamentals
  and applications in deep learning and educational technologies.
  The project combines Jupyter notebooks, explanatory markdowns, and illustrative
  examples for educators and students. Notebooks are pedagogically structured with
  learning objectives, prerequisites, and module summaries.
  Licensed under Creative Commons BY-NC-SA 4.0.

  This work is inspired by and builds upon Daniel Bourke's "Zero to Mastery Learn
  PyTorch for Deep Learning" course (learnpytorch.io), which is licensed under
  MIT License. The original concepts, reorganized, translated into Turkish, and
  adapted for educational technology audiences with new pedagogical structure.
